                    <span>This book is nothing more than a re-hash of things from other books. A large portion of this book is nothing more than quotes from the book "The forgotten Soldier" by Guy Sajer. Interspersed is the authors "opinion" of what the various quotes mean. Not very historical if you ask me. All in all, it is just barely interesting, and also one of the least informative that I've ever read.</span>
                  
              
